author: @KintounKal
text:
I just heard about and supported a petition to save Star Wars toy designer Mark Boudreaux who designed Kennerâ€™s Millennium Falcon. Laura Lee Aguilar started it 4 weeks ago and provided the following details. 

Mark Boudreaux is currently at the Bethesda North Hospital in Ohio, having been there for over a year on a ventilator as treatment for covid, which "appears to contradict every health care standard when it comes to ventilator use." (as reported by the Epoch Times article, 'Star Wars Toy Designer's Galactic Battle over Covid ventilator use' - March 9, 2023) Mark is in a catch-22 here, as the extreme amount of time on the ventilator has destroyed his lungs, causing him to require a lung transplant that he is not eligible for because of the destruction of his lungs and health as a consequence of his treatment at Bethesda North. 

This beloved toy designer and his wife have exhausted every avenue of assistance in their cause, except for their fellow Americans who can come alongside them to put a spotlight on the parties that can alleviate the suffering of their patient. There oath requires that 'first, they do no harm' - but if they fail in their oath, they should do everything in their power to restore the health that their actions and protocols have diminished. This man wants to live! In appreciation for all he has done for us through his talent and designs, let us help him to truly enjoy the rest of his life as a healthy human being again. We petition Bethesda North to seek every avenue possible in providing Mark Boudreaux with the lung transplant he needs to live. 

At the moment, we only need 443 more signatures to reach the next goal. Please chip in $2 to distribute this petition or share with one other person instead by copying the link via Facebook, WhatsApp, Twitter, Email, or Messenger.

author: @miksss_
text:
My own opinion:

First, Popularity and achievements are from their fans. You streamed their songs multiple times, watched their mvs and buy their albums. Meanwhile, we don't care about any of that. Yes, we do care about our faves achievements and we do try to make them win by voting but not to the point that we're going to waste our time watching the same my for an hour or so. They don't force us too. They remind us that we have a life aside from them.

Second, recognition is also based on popularity. My faves get recognised because of their talents. Their vocals, their sense of style, their versatile acting, their dance styles. They have a life beside shitloads of comebacks and our faves can stand alone without the help of their members. For example: EXO Baekhyun could be BYUN BAEKHYUN as a soloist, as an actor, a luxury brand ambassador.

And I'm proud to say that this is what EXO taught us. We didn't have so many views in an my bcs they always remind us that we should focus on ourselves first or study first than watching their ig lives, them who always tell us to buy foods instead of alburns, and most especially having their own unique talent in their solo activities with us making us all proud as EXO-LS

text: I know some of us are so busy with their school and work and those are important in life. But please let's str3@m harder everyday at least once a day. author: @letmeshowur90slooooooove76
text:
Information: This is not just a song it is a collaboration between SM Ent. and Disney for the Star Wars movie as an advertisement for them 

â€As billboard explained:

â€The force is with one of Korea's biggest pop acts.

â€The forthcoming Star Wars: Episode VII - The Force Awakens movie has teamed up with EXO for a collaboration. After the film franchise teased a K-pop partnership on Facebook, the results came via the new song "Lightsaber" and a cinematic music video.


â€Opening with Darth Vader's iconic breathing, "Lightsaber" begins with a racing, synth-pop sound that grows into a frenetic EDM breakdown. Despite the high-energy production, there's a hint of melancholy here as the guys sing about being a girls "lifesaver" and their "lightsaber" -- nice play on words -- and bring her out of her darkness.

author: @yellowchimp
text: This concept of modern Day Jedi is a show I would watch. I imagine the fall of the Jedi religion to be overcome with a rebellious generation born with strength in the force, but no respect for it. Hence the power they have over others, and queue the drama that ensues. Baekhyun is the inspiration behind most of that. Him messing up that shop. Kai with the burden of inheriting the reputation and struggling to survive a harsh existence he never wanted to be a part of. Something like the parents building a castle/company/wealth with the dishonest manipulation of their power with the force. Now with his parents dead he has to try to defend it, if not himself. Sehun is giving off a hunter vibe. He could be hunting down someone for revenge, a fellow Jedi. Oooooooooooh and the red in the end makes me think they are all being hunted by the same thing. SO. Sehun is hunting the hunter. This hunter connects all members together. They eventually join forces to defeat a common evil.

[spread to all EXOL]
We All Should Know smth about streaming on YouTube :
 Each click on the mv link befor 300th views will be count as a view 

*using the same IP your views will only be counted once every 6-8 h -so we can't broke any record-

*bc you can't switch the IP address of your device the bestÂ  & only way is share the mv on SNS or your website so everytime the video will get played it will count as one view

ğŸ””HOW TO STREAM ON YT WITH THIS METHOD:

1-go to youtube or youtube app

2-search for the mv you want to stream (EXO TEMPO MV)

3-start the mv

4-scroll down n click on SHARE and on EMBED

5-copy the whole text and go to facebook

6-paste the text & post it (make sure for the mv to actually show up)

7-now go to your facebook post and watch the mv as often as you can. Youtube can't track your IP anymore.

author: @wednesdayunderwood4488
text: This is going to sound so weird, mostly because it is, but this is like my third hour of trying to get into EXO (I'd say it's going pretty well) I already know all of their names and have listened to and watched a lot of their MVs, however, something I've noticed, (here's the weird part) Baekhyun has beautiful dental structure and just overall great teeth. You're now probably thinking, "WOOOWW when you said 'weird' you meant *weird*" and yes, you are correct, sorry I'm a dental student and I have a huge fascination with teeth. Truly, since I was young I would assess and analyze other people's teeth along with my own. Also, I know, it's an odd thing to say and, well, to notice in the first place but it's true, he has great dental structure. I like how his cuspids are sharp but his {central} incisors are well rounded to a flat kind of look, and they're long but not so long that they hardly fit in his mouth, and especially his lower row of teeth, holy moly those are gorgeous. His cuspids and second and first bicuspids on both sides are so beautiful, also something I noticed is that his cuspids and second bicuspids on both the top and bottom are longer than the rest and are pointed which gives an almost fang-like vibe to them and it's incredibly attractive. Along with amazing structure, they're well-kempt and sparkling white. Ugh, what I would give to get a closer look at his molars you have no clue. Along with all of that his jaw naturally comes out slightly farther than his upper row of teeth but it's not like he has an underbite and when he speaks his jawline pops and shows off his gorgeous teeth. Anyway, so that's the end of my obsession rant about Baekhyun's teeth, thanks for reading.

author: @brunobucciaralick3914
text: Guys... I'll never get over, because they've been the reason why I stayed into the whole kpop scene back in 2012... And it still hurts and I've spent almost 2 years hating them with a passion and cursing them.. But my heart earns for them, even if it's ot9 nine now.. I feel horribly guilty as a tao stan, and it hurts a lot to watch all the new stuff, like I still had hopes back then when this came out.. It will never be the same as it was like back then, I won't ever be the hardcore exol I used to be, but.. Everyday I find myself humming their songs, or look through funny videos on insta and realize I've been staring at 20 exo videos in a row.. I guess new fans don't understand the pain, or anyone who's not been a Chinese line stan.. I slowly accepted them at the end of last year again, and now I'm falling all over.. I can't keep myself away from them. They have been and will be the only group for me, and I'm hella mad at myself and my feelings for betraying me like this :/

author: @jasni16
text:
I'm an ELF but I really started to like Exo. I avoided exo because of all the hype that surrounds them. Turns out I found a new fandom. Still gonna take a while to learn all their names and faces though. 
 And I don't understand why people keep saying there should be more star wars in the MV. I'm a star wars fan and I thought the MV was amazing. It was just a promotional song. The goal is to expose star wars to a new fan base and if they had added too much of the movie and not enough exo, many fans would lose interest. Fans would first want to see their idols and the rest follow. It could have included more of the duel with lightsabers...but honestly, I think people would check out the movie if it was left to imagination...curiosity is the goal, and this video achieved it.

author: @Saffion
text:
Sorry about this. Please read on if you wish.

When EXO first debuted, they decided to sit in strange places like a shed and an abandoned building. They wondered to themselves, "What Is Love?" Each member met up, saw an eclipse, and became transported to another planet. They named it EXO Planet, and decided to dance like never before. That was the planet's first ever "History." One day, everyone found out that they had powers. Chanyeol saw his hands burning up from his power. "MAMA" he screamed. EXO was then transported to a completely white area, where there was one rule: Let out the "WOLF". In a garage nearby, the maknae, Sehun, finally learned how to talk. "Eu...reu....rong.....?" he said. "Yes" said Suho. "Growl." Months later, it became Christmas. D.O., Baekhyun, Chen, and Luhan sang with a piano in the middle of a white wasteland. Everyone else was Christmas shopping for their "Miracles in December", and Tao turned back time to when they were stuck in a labyrinth. Kai was the one to get everyone out, and they all woke up in another garage, which was a car wash. Everyone was on "Overdose", and they sang out to the love of their lives. Not knowing that they were still on drugs, they repeatedly sang "Call Me Baby" until they woke up again. After a huge football game, everyone was enraged. Members swung at a beer bottle with bats, and Kai, Chanyeol, and Sehun were all sitting in a meth lab with smoke everywhere. Once again, they were high. This time, they sang "Love Me Right" over and over again. Sehun left for the roof to think about his life, so he went to his motorcycle and committed suicide. Baekhyun was still high, so he knocked everything over in a nearby grocery store. Kai was hungover, so he left for the train station, where he could kick up dust like a "Lightsaber."

text: Exo is cool.Â  BIGBANG is cool.Â  Personally I'm a really big VIP but I like Exo too and a lot of other bands and I really don't understand all the hate and strife between different fan groups.Â  I'm seeing a lot of angry people because BIGBANG is winning over EXO and yeah, I get why you might be a little upset.Â  It's your favorite band, you want them to win, and it's great that you vote for them to help them.Â  But why trash another band just because your favorite didn't win?Â  If BIGBANG lost to someone I'd be like, "Well, that's a pity but it's okay, y'all all still my favorite.Â  Congratulations to the winner."Â  Why can't we just do that instead of yelling hate at everyone?Â  Come on haters, getÂ a life.Â  As for this song, I really do like it!Â  The "No concealed lightsabers" sign was just awesome :p

author: @Nopahhh
text:
Kai is the one that turns bad, right? His white bandage gets soaked in blood, whose color blends in with the dark T-shirt he is wearing in the tub. Then in the next scene, his blood seems darker and honestly I don't know who Kai saw when he turns around from the mirror, but something happened and he decides to put on a black jacket. Baekhyun and Sehun both have white outfits n from the beginning to the end, although Sehun seems to be more perfect of a Jedai than Baekhyun based on his actions, the color of his outfit and how he is admitted to the Jedai bar. 

The only time anyone in this videos lights up the lightsaber is the very last scene, where the "dark" Kai sticks it out as the elevator door opens. Based on how Baekhyun was inside the convenience store, Kai propbably didn't go to Baekhyun directly, but we know that Kai is attacking some Jedai and both Baekhyun and Sehun are in trouble. Especially Sehun, since he tried to reach for a lightsaber he gave to the bouncer? guy in the beginning. 

What I don't get is who Kai saw after turning around from the mirror, who Baekhyun received the call from, and if it has anything to do with the next Star Wars movie. Also, while this was a super cool video that went with the song and EXO's debut concept of being the ones from the "Exoplanet" outer space, I don't understand what this plot line has to do with anything.

author: @Moopies
text: I figured it out guys~ A Vader figure is the bad guy. In the beginning there is the breathing and in the end there is the reflection of the Vader figure in the elevator. presumably Kai Sehun and Baekhyun are all dead, cuz Kai disappeared when the lights came back on, and Jedi disappear when they die (also, blue sabers were classically Jedi). Sehun was a Jedi/Good guy cuz he was able to go to the Jedi only bar, he was snuck up on and presumably killed since he was saberless. Then Baekhyun was just waiting to be killed, I think he might have been in cahoots with the bad guys, since he was all ragey and carelessly swinging his lightsaber around; and they were all attacked by a red saber (implied by the glowing red) which is classically a Sith thing. So Exo are all cool modern Jedi dudes, and now they are dead because Some modern Darth Vader killed them all...

text: The more I watch this MV, the more I believe that all the EXO members in this MV are jedis living in modern day. Kai might be playing two roles - one is the injured, vulnerable jedi and the other is a Sith. Sehun and Baekhyun are two jedis who are trying to lead normal lives. Baekhyun's character seems to be having some kind of internal conflict, whereas Sehun's character has more control - perhaps he adjusted better to human life than Baekhyun's character does. Towards the end of the MV, you see them sensing danger as Darth Kai wields his lightsaber. I hope there is a part two of this MV :)

author: @Angrarim
text:
I like EXO and I'm a star wars fanatics, but I found myself confused about this collab.

This collaboration heavily favors EXO rather being in the common grounds. 
I was hoping they would at least promotes the star wars universe (at least wears jedi robe, lightsaber duels, rebel attire, mandalorian armor... heck, even stormtrooper armor I'll take it) to the Exo-L rather than using the lightsaber reference just to promote the song's name.

There's not even 50% of star wars references put into this MV to be passable as a "collab".

I know EXO is not the one at fault in this part, they only take the company's direction and I appreciate SM and Disney's attempt to collab with both parties but this... is kind of half-assing.

The force is not strong with this MV.

author: @jn3259
text:
!!! Everyone, EXO is competing in 4/5 categories BigBang is in, and although we used to spearhead at least 2 categories by a *good margin*, they've *completely turned the tables* and are now leading by *far more* than that amount. 

Please, we're a big fandom, but we ARE losing to a group that's ALREADY set to win a good number of categories, while EXO will have 0 WINS if our complacency perpetuates.

EXO has been concerting nonstop, theyâ€™ve released incredible comebacks this year and theyâ€™re all dead on their feet from how tired they are -- from everything they've done for us. They deserve something for their hard work. You know they wonâ€™t push us to vote for them, but we know this is one thing they want and itâ€™s our annual chance to show them our appreciation and love in the BEST way we know how -- and it IS within reach if we just try. For all their hard work this whole year, we only have to put in a monthâ€™s worth of effort thatâ€™s meagre in comparison. Please, letâ€™s reciprocate everything theyâ€™ve done for us this year and spoil them as much as they have us. What would everything they've done this year amount to, if their fans are not showing due support? How would they *feel*? They'll try to say that it's alright, it can't be helped, but we know they'll be disappointed and they're completely dependent on us to win /something/.

author: @MzPunky
text: Most people were expecting a big production but I'm pretty satisfied with this. I would have loved a longer MV but I like that this was "nod" to Star Wars and that it didn't turn into some corny Sci Fi MV. Now that would have been disastrous. The Jedis were subtly integrated into our modern world and I thought that was pretty cool. Sometimes less is more. Judging from their hair color, this was LMR era and was probably filmed in between touring, so that could explain why we didn't get something more detailed. Star Wars is my first love ( I grew up on this ok ) so this was a smooth move SM and I caught most of the sounds they mixed the song which was a clever addition. Darth Vader breathing, lightsabers, R2D2, and speeder bikes!

author: @WindiKuhn
text:
The song was nice, but after seeing what the lyrics mean, it just makes me think that the song was originally supposed to be called "Life Saver" and that they just changed the lyrics to "Lightsaber". "Lightsaber" makes absolutely NO sense in the song at all. And the video wasn't what was expected, I expected lightsaber fights, not EXO carrying around lightsaber hilts like they were fuckin purses or some shit.
Makes me think that Disney didn't even know what the song was about & just thought "hey, let's do a collaboration with this kpop group  cuz they have a song called "Lightsaber" & they have lightsaber hilts & we're releasing a Star Wars film next month!" Ugh. This was a huge disappointment for me. I am a huge Star Wars fan and I just expected something better, like the lyrics & MV being more about Star Wars, or something!
Now , that I gave this a listen, I am gonna go back and play SWTOR some more.

author: @javitocr7
text: This video is such a let down. I actually really like the song and I think it could have worked wonders if only the video had had at least a lightsaber battle and more Star Wars references other than turned off sabers and a 'JEDI ONLY' sign. I was so looking forward to this video as an equally huge Star Wars and EXO fan, mostly because these 3 are my biases, but honestly, you could watch only the teaser and get a solid idea of the entire video. As someone who is very passionate about music video production I must say that if your video can be summed up in 30 seconds and you don't make the best out of every second, then you're doing a very plain and shitty job. Plus considering the song is longer and you can clearly tell by how the video is edited, it looks even sloppier and like whichever crew was pulling this off got bored half way through the project (I wouldn't blame them considering how much plot planning it lacks and the amount of key elements it's missing). C'mon, SM, we've all seen the MAMA music video along with many other projects of yours, we KNOW you can work some magic with audiovisual effects. I can't believe you even thought this was a good enough idea to invest money on.

author: @nynalinn
text: I hate to say it but... that's it? No epic lightsaber battle? Heard the full song and it's great but really not happy with how D.O. was left out during the highlight/climax of their song again. I was waiting to hear him after the bridge, singing with Baekhyun and Chen, but nothing. Frustrating really, when you know he can hit those notes dead on too. What Is Love proved that. At this rate, I'll never be able to hear his upper range. I feel like he's been demoted from main vocal to just vocal. His parts lately haven't been challenging, even his ad libs. Singing in his comfort zone and not really exploring more with his voice. It's holding him back vocally.

author: @katyali9527
text:
Guys, it was kinda shorter than usual, because that`s not even a single, it`s just a promo-song, which will be played during captions - on contrary it has to be short, dynamic and catchy. So it is. Though I didn`t understand the scenes in mv, I am asking Star Wars fans not to take it too seriously, because it`s rather made for EXO-Ls pleasure ( and the photosession too) and has nothing to do with movie promotions. The movie itself just needed a song. No need to seek meaning in music videos, that`s in 90% an eye-candy.
I am very content with the song, Chanyeol`s rap is so dope here and I heard a lot of Kai`s voice, which is really pleasant.
BTW Kai in a suit  - it just hurtsss TTTTTTT That back and shoulders...
The audio itself is for 3 minutes 4 seconds though. This MV is obviously just a gift for us, EXO-ls, considering that not all the members were free to film it, they still filmed it even with three members, let`s be grateful.

And they should have had more build up for Yeols rap. Somehow using his height, like have his shadow  slowly appear in an alley. He could be the villain with a red light saber. Other than that it was PERFECT! I love how Baek sets the scifi feel  for the mv. Soo's voice also does this through out. Givin me chills and shit. Then Jongins sofisticated scenes, and his fuckin sweet dance break. Like he's practicing his fighting or something. Now I'm sad thinking of what Tao could have done for this theme.
